Approach:-
Use sliding window (two pointers).

- Expand the window using right and store frequency of a, b, c.
- When the window contains all three characters, add n - right to the answer because all ending positions after right will form valid substrings.
- Shrink the window from the left to find smaller valid windows.

Code:-
class Solution(object):
    def compress(self, chars):
        n = len(chars)
        read = 0
        write = 0
        while read < n:
            current = chars[read]
            cnt = 0
            while (read < n and chars[read] == current):
                cnt+=1
                read+=1
            chars[write] = current
            write+=1
            if cnt >1:
                for digit in str(cnt):
                    chars[write]=digit
                    write+=1

        return write

Time Complexity : O(n)
Space Complexity : O(1)
